HEADWORD: Wurbagool
<hw>Wur"ba*gool</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A fruit bat (<spn>Pteropus medius</spn>) native of India. It is
similar to the flying fox, but smaller.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

